HOW TO USE THE GOLDEN RATIO MEASURING SYSTEM TO CREATE BEAUTIFUL EYEBROWS. 

Beauty trends come and go. So do eyebrow shapes and styles. When you’re in the eyebrow microblading industry, it’s important to know how to adapt to these changing trends.

Luckily we have the golden ratio measuring system which is a fail-proof foundation in creating the perfect eyebrow shape.

Before we discuss the microblading golden ratio, let’s first take a look at its foundation–the mathematical golden ratio or what I like to call the "divine proportion"

The golden ratio is a geometric ratio that has been used in architecture, art, and design for centuries. It originated in Euclidean geometry and is epitomized in famous works such as Leonardo da Vinci’s Mona Lisa, the Pyramids of Giza, and the Parthenon.

The ratio is found throughout nature as well, often in plant leaves and petals. According to both mathematicians and artists, the golden ratio defines the perfect proportion because it can create shapes with the most pleasing balance and appearance.

While artists in various fields might agree that the golden ratio is a universally effective method, you must use your best judgment when using it for eyebrow shaping. As with any technique, you must use the concept as a guide instead of solely relying on it. Listen to what your client wants and consider their unique facial features, then apply the golden ratio to find the perfect brow shape that suits their face. You will learn more about this technique and its practical applications when you enroll in our classes.

My top 4 tips for a precise and successful “SECOND PASS”👇

If you are an artist beginner or advance still struggling with precision and good implantation of color this is for you!

Are your healed results still inconsistent?, are you doing a lot of work at the touchup visit? Then keep on reading! If this post is helpful like and share with a fellow colleague and if you want me to continue sharing these kind of tips comment below.

SO WHY IS PRECISION SO IMPORTANT?

When we work precisely we will start to see great healed results on most skintypes however through experience you will learn that some skintypes do better with microblading than others but if you incorporate these tips your well on your way to seeing better healed results.

✨3 POINT STRETCH
Reference the video above to see the proper way to stretch. Your stretching hand (the one without the tool) consists of the middle and Index finger and your pinky of the hand with the tool to stretch the skin in 3 opposite direction. This will hold the skin flat and taught. Remember, the better the stretch the more fine and smooth your cut will be.

MASTER TIP: Do not stretch in the same direction of the stroke, this will close the stroke making it hard to feel the channel. Instead stretch the skin in the opposite direction to open the stroke and this will allow you to feel the channel.

✨ PIGMENT PICKUP
Again if you reference back to the video notice the small dot of pigment we pick up using the tip of the blade. Little pigment pickup will allow you to visibly see where your blade is landing inside the stroke. 

MASTER TIP: use the tip of the blade when doing your second pass, because it’s not the sharpest part of your blade you will be able to implant without creating a deeper cut.

✨ SHIMMY MOVEMENT
Look at the video above and notice the back and fourth movement we are doing, we have found that this method is the best way to drop the most amount of the pigment into the stroke.

MASTER TIP: Do not rush this step, this is the most important part to ensure great healed results!

✨GOOD LIGHTING
 This helps illuminate your strokes so that they are more visible when implanting. You can never have enough lighting.
